I now have all the information needed. Here is the complete analysis.

---

## Analysis: Source String Flow Across the Codebase

### Overview

The `source` field identifies which coding agent produced a session transcript. Two values exist today: `"claude_code"` and `"codex"`. The value originates from adapter class properties in `packages/agent-adapters`, flows through the shared API contract in `packages/api-routes`, is transmitted by the CLI during uploads, dispatches to the correct adapter on the API server, and is ultimately hardcoded into ClickHouse materialized views that populate the `session_analytics` table.

---

### 1. Where Source Values Are Defined (Adapter Classes)

There are exactly two adapter implementations, each declaring a `source` string property:

**Claude Code Adapter**
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/agent-adapters/src/adapters/claude-code/index.ts:141`
```ts
class ClaudeCodeAdapter implements AgentAdapter {
    name = "Claude Code";
    source = "claude_code";
    rawTableName = "rudel.claude_sessions";
```

**Codex Adapter**
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/agent-adapters/src/adapters/codex/index.ts:88-91`
```ts
class CodexAdapter implements AgentAdapter {
    name = "OpenAI Codex";
    source = "codex";
    rawTableName = "rudel.codex_sessions";
```

Both are exported as singleton instances:
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/agent-adapters/src/adapters/claude-code/index.ts:367` -- `export const claudeCodeAdapter = new ClaudeCodeAdapter();`
- `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/agent-adapters/src/adapters/codex/index.ts:254` -- `export const codexAdapter = new CodexAdapter();`

---

### 2. Where Source Is Used as a Type (Interfaces, Zod Schemas, Generated Types)

#### AgentAdapter interface
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/agent-adapters/src/types.ts:45-48`
```ts
export interface AgentAdapter {
    name: string;
    source: string;
    rawTableName: string;
```
The `source` property is typed as plain `string` -- there is no enum or union type constraining the values.

#### ScannedProject interface
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/agent-adapters/src/types.ts:12-18`
```ts
export interface ScannedProject {
    source: string;
    projectPath: string;
    displayPath: string;
    sessions: SessionFile[];
    sessionCount: number;
}
```
This carries the source string alongside discovered session data.

#### IngestSessionInputSchema (Zod, shared API contract)
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/api-routes/src/index.ts:89-102`
```ts
export const IngestSessionInputSchema = z.object({
    source: z.string().default("claude_code"),
    sessionId: z.string(),
    projectPath: z.string(),
    // ...
});
```
The `source` field is `z.string()` with a default of `"claude_code"`. This means if a client omits `source`, it defaults to `"claude_code"`. The inferred TypeScript type is:
```ts
export type IngestSessionInput = z.infer<typeof IngestSessionInputSchema>;
```
at line 109.

#### SessionAnalyticsSchema (Zod, analytics output)
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/api-routes/src/schemas/analytics.ts:251-273`
```ts
export const SessionAnalyticsSchema = z.object({
    // ...
    source: z.string().optional(),
});
```
Line 272: `source` is `z.string().optional()` on the read side for analytics listing results.

#### SessionDetailSchema (Zod, session detail output)
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/api-routes/src/schemas/analytics.ts:350-372`
```ts
export const SessionDetailSchema = z.object({
    // ...
    source: z.string().optional(),
});
```
Line 371: also `z.string().optional()`.

#### SessionListInputSchema (Zod, filter parameter)
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/api-routes/src/schemas/analytics.ts:294-305`
```ts
export const SessionListInputSchema = DaysInputSchema.extend({
    // ...
    source: z.string().optional(),
    // ...
});
```
Line 298: `source` is an optional filter parameter for the session list endpoint.

#### RudelSessionAnalyticsRow (generated ClickHouse type)
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/ch-schema/src/generated/chkit-types.ts:78-118`
```ts
export interface RudelSessionAnalyticsRow {
    // ...
    source: string
    // ...
}
```
Line 102: `source` is a required `string` field in the `session_analytics` row type.

#### RudelSessionAnalyticsRowSchema (generated Zod)
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/ch-schema/src/generated/chkit-types.ts:120-160`
```ts
export const RudelSessionAnalyticsRowSchema = z.object({
    // ...
    source: z.string(),
    // ...
});
```
Line 144: `source` is `z.string()`.

#### FailedUpload interface
`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/apps/cli/src/lib/failed-uploads.ts:6-15`
```ts
export interface FailedUpload {
    sessionId: string;
    transcriptPath: string;
