`/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/ch-schema/src/db/schema/codex-sessions.ts:73`
```sql
'codex' as source,
```

Both MVs write into the same target table (`rudel.session_analytics`), and the `source` column in that table has a `LowCardinality(String)` type with a default of `'claude_code'` and an index (`idx_source`) for efficient filtering.

#### Analytics Read Path (source exposed to frontend)

The `SessionListInputSchema` at `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/packages/api-routes/src/schemas/analytics.ts:298` accepts an optional `source` filter. However, the session list handler at `/Users/marc/conductor/workspaces/rudel/london/apps/api/src/handlers/analytics/sessions.ts:18-31` does not currently pass the `source` filter through to the service function -- it passes `user_id`, `project_path`, and `repository` but not `source`. The `SessionAnalyticsSchema` (line 272) and `SessionDetailSchema` (line 371) both include `source: z.string().optional()` in their output shapes, so the value is available when queried from `session_analytics`.

The web frontend (`apps/web`) does not reference `"claude_code"` or `"codex"` anywhere in its source code.

---

### Summary: Complete Source Value Map

| Value | Defined at | Hardcoded locations |
|-------|-----------|-------------------|
| `"claude_code"` | `ClaudeCodeAdapter.source` (agent-adapters) | Zod default (api-routes:90), MV SQL (ch-schema session-analytics.ts:175), column default (ch-schema session-analytics.ts:47), migration SQL (20260302...sql:13,52), 3 test files |
| `"codex"` | `CodexAdapter.source` (agent-adapters) | MV SQL (ch-schema codex-sessions.ts:73), migration SQL (20260302...sql:48), CLI hook (turn-complete.ts:75) |

### Data Flow Diagram

```
CLI / Hook
    |
    v
adapter.buildUploadRequest()        <-- sets source = this.source ("claude_code" or "codex")
    |
    v
IngestSessionInput { source: "..." } <-- validated by IngestSessionInputSchema (default "claude_code")
    |
    v  (HTTP POST /rpc)
API router.ts:86
    |
    v
getAdapter(input.source)             <-- registry lookup by source string
    |
    v
adapter.ingest()
    |
    +--> ingestRudelClaudeSessions()  --> rudel.claude_sessions  (no source column)
    |                                       |
    |                                       v
    |                                  session_analytics_mv  --> rudel.session_analytics (source = 'claude_code')
    |
    +--> ingestRudelCodexSessions()   --> rudel.codex_sessions   (no source column)
                                            |
                                            v
                                       codex_session_analytics_mv --> rudel.session_analytics (source = 'codex')
```

The raw tables (`claude_sessions`, `codex_sessions`) do not have a `source` column. The `source` value is injected only at the materialized view level when rows flow from the raw tables into the unified `session_analytics` table.

